WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:05.087
Welcome to Life Church.

00:05.488 --> 00:09.052
We're here to help you become who God created you to be, and we'd love to hear from you.

00:09.112 --> 00:15.580
Take a quick survey at life.church slash podcast connect to let us know how we can support you on your faith journey.

00:15.960 --> 00:17.322
And now let's go to the message.

00:22.428 --> 00:31.819
Well, sadly, when many people think of church today, they don't think of loving people.

00:33.241 --> 00:34.162
Unfortunately,

00:34.242 --> 00:36.665
Sometimes they don't think of kind people.

00:38.246 --> 00:41.250
They don't think of generous people.

00:41.270 --> 00:52.142
Sadly, if you ask lots of people today to describe Christians, they're gonna say things like angry, narrow, judgmental.

00:53.263 --> 01:00.110
That certainly bothers our Heavenly Father, and that should bother us as well.

01:00.971 --> 01:03.634
Because if people don't experience love,

01:04.610 --> 01:10.197
They're not gonna experience God because our God is love.

01:11.278 --> 01:15.223
And we're in a very important message series for our church community.

01:15.263 --> 01:19.889
Today is the final message in the series, a church that pleases God.

01:20.610 --> 01:27.458
And we're talking about that's really the cry of our heart, that we wanna be a church that honors God, pleases God in all that we do.

01:27.498 --> 01:33.105
And if you've been paying attention in previous weeks, what is a church that pleases God?

01:33.245 --> 01:34.066
It's made up of?

01:34.754 --> 01:37.116
people that are pleasing God.

01:37.457 --> 01:44.384
And today I want to talk about a very important quality of a church and a group of people that pleases God and the truth is this.

01:45.265 --> 01:51.731
A church that pleases God is made up of people who love like Jesus.

01:52.532 --> 01:56.756
It's made up of people who are loving like Jesus.

01:57.136 --> 02:02.642
That yes, loving can be telling the truth, but loving is telling the truth in love.

02:02.946 --> 02:07.051
And Jesus said it very, very plainly in John 13, verses 34 and 35.

02:07.332 --> 02:11.477
He said, a new command I give to you, let's all say it together, what's the command?

02:11.737 --> 02:13.960
He said, love one another.

02:14.020 --> 02:15.041
Now how do you do that?

02:15.061 --> 02:20.668
He said, as I have loved you, so you must love one another.

02:20.708 --> 02:28.338
And he says by this, by love, not just by your theology or your worship style or how smart you are,

02:28.546 --> 02:35.901
But by love, by this, everyone will know that you are on my disciples if you love one another.

02:36.262 --> 02:38.547
A new command I give to you above all else.

02:38.607 --> 02:43.597
Love the Lord your God with all your heart, all your mind, all your soul, all your strength, and love your neighbor as yourself.

02:44.078 --> 02:47.685
According to Jesus, love isn't optional.

02:48.587 --> 02:49.970
Love is the evidence.

02:50.498 --> 02:51.640
It's a reflection.

02:51.760 --> 02:56.447
We love as we've been loved, and that shows that we belong to God.

02:56.828 --> 03:09.208
And when we read the Gospels, one thing becomes unmistakably clear, that Jesus was drawn to a lot of the people that the religious leaders actually avoided.

03:09.989 --> 03:10.730
Who did he love?

03:10.770 --> 03:18.162
Yes, he loved everyone, but you'll see Jesus drawn to very specifically, love those who were broken.

03:18.946 --> 03:21.488
He loved those that were hurting.

03:22.329 --> 03:29.696
He forgave the people who were very, very sinful, and everyone else said, they're too sinful for the church, and Jesus forgave their sins and loved them.

03:29.716 --> 03:36.343
He included the outcast, and even the people everyone ran from, he actually would have walked to.

03:37.524 --> 03:48.434
God is pleased when His church looks like His Son, because Jesus didn't just say He loves people, He did just say it.

03:49.090 --> 03:51.993
but he demonstrated it in the way that he lived.

03:52.594 --> 03:56.478
And that's why today I'm really, really excited to do something special.

03:56.538 --> 04:04.107
We call it a team teach weekend, where I'm going to open up and then I'm gonna introduce your campus pastor.

04:04.127 --> 04:14.198
And I wanna tell you right now, I am so thankful for your pastor, for the integrity, for the passion, for the love and the heart for people.

04:14.739 --> 04:17.522
And if you're new, I promise you, you're gonna feel it.

04:17.826 --> 04:24.738
Your pastor prays for you, your pastor loves you, and your pastor wants to show you the love of God.

04:25.098 --> 04:38.962
And so today, would you just give a really warm, really, really, really excited welcome to your campus pastor.

04:40.994 --> 04:42.677
Pastor Craig couldn't have said it better.

04:42.817 --> 04:45.381
I genuinely love you so, so much.

04:45.421 --> 04:46.423
And I love my pastor.

04:46.463 --> 04:49.327
Pastor Craig, thank you for the opportunity to team teach with you.

04:49.348 --> 04:50.890
I mean, who gets that opportunity, right?

04:50.910 --> 04:54.917
What an incredible privilege it is to share God's word with His people.

04:55.137 --> 04:58.442
And I want to take a moment to just recognize that we're here in Edmond, Oklahoma.

04:58.542 --> 05:02.409
We're also joined by people all over the world at Life Church online.

05:02.429 --> 05:04.672
We've got a couple of locations joining us as well.

05:04.692 --> 05:05.714
I just want to take a moment to

05:05.762 --> 05:09.227
Thank you for joining us today as we hear God's word.

05:09.247 --> 05:13.532
Can we show some love to the people joining us all around the world from every single country?

05:15.034 --> 05:22.364
You know, when Pastor Craig talked to me about this message, I genuinely got really excited and I also got kind of nervous.

05:23.045 --> 05:27.031
And I'm excited because I am a product of a loving church.

05:27.051 --> 05:31.817
And I'm a little nervous, actually really nervous, but I'll tell you more about that here in a moment.

05:32.438 --> 05:35.602
I wanna just take a moment to just recognize that today.

05:35.682 --> 05:59.858
It's a really tough day and it's a tough time in our world and God calls us to love people and this can be really challenging and that's why I'm a little nervous because today I might say some things that you might not like and you might not even like me by the end of this and that makes me a little nervous because I kind of want you to like me but I also want you to hear God's word.

06:00.194 --> 06:05.963
And so before we jump into all of that, I do want to introduce you to the person who doesn't just like me, but she loves me.

06:06.443 --> 06:11.691
My best friend, my wife Liz, this May, we will celebrate 24 years of marriage.

06:12.372 --> 06:15.237
And I love her so much.

06:16.178 --> 06:18.722
But I want to show you a picture before it even started.

06:18.742 --> 06:20.825
This was way back before we even dated.

06:21.406 --> 06:24.210
This is us as teenagers at a church camp.

06:24.290 --> 06:29.517
And if you ask her, she says that I asked her to take a picture, but I was a rapper at the time.

06:29.537 --> 06:30.438
You can see the microphone.

06:30.758 --> 06:36.505
So I think she was a fan and she just wanted a picture with me, but I love my wife so much.

06:36.525 --> 06:42.833
And when I think about those two young people, I recognize that both of us, we are a product of a loving church.

06:43.034 --> 06:47.179
Our life has been impacted by God's love through his people, through the church.

06:47.239 --> 06:52.946
And today, I wanna take a moment to show you two stories about two guys,

06:53.442 --> 06:54.724
so that you'll learn two truths.

06:55.545 --> 06:58.168
So if you are a note taker, I'm helping you out right now.

06:58.208 --> 06:59.429
This is how you map out your notes.

06:59.750 --> 07:04.495
Two stories about two guys, so you'll learn two truths.

07:04.515 --> 07:07.699
And the first story is found in Mark chapter two.

07:07.859 --> 07:14.668
Now, whenever the Bible doesn't name somebody, I kinda like to put a name in there just because it makes it a little more relatable to me.

07:14.688 --> 07:18.232
So we find our first story in Mark chapter two.

07:18.492 --> 07:20.054
So we're gonna give this guy a name, okay?

07:20.414 --> 07:22.076
And his name's gonna be Benito.

07:22.237 --> 07:23.378
Everybody say Benito.

07:24.546 --> 07:27.710
Okay, for those of you that don't speak Spanish, let me translate, it's Benito.

07:28.031 --> 07:29.573
Okay, I have Benito.

07:29.593 --> 07:30.915
Let's just call him Benny, okay?

07:30.935 --> 07:31.896
This is Benny, all right?

07:31.916 --> 07:33.278
So let's read scripture.

07:33.358 --> 07:36.262
Mark chapter two, verses one through three.

07:36.322 --> 07:42.210
It says, when Jesus again entered Capernaum, the people heard that he had come home.

07:42.811 --> 07:48.158
They gathered in such large numbers that there was no room left, not even outside the door.

07:48.819 --> 07:50.882
And Jesus preached the word to them.

07:51.663 --> 07:53.906
Some men came, bringing to him,

07:53.986 --> 07:55.067
a paralyzed man.

07:55.087 --> 07:56.789
This is Benny, okay?

07:57.549 --> 07:58.971
Carried by four of them.

08:00.052 --> 08:09.000
Since they could not get him to Jesus because of the crowd, they made an opening in the roof above Jesus by digging through it and then lowered the man the man was lying on.

08:09.561 --> 08:12.604
When Jesus saw their faith, this is really important.

08:12.804 --> 08:14.005
I need you to remember this scripture.

08:14.045 --> 08:23.154
When Jesus saw their faith, he said to the paralyzed man, son, your sins are forgiven.

08:24.066 --> 08:26.650
Benny was paralyzed.

08:28.192 --> 08:32.839
And back then, that created some feelings around paralyzed people.

08:32.919 --> 08:34.461
Like, people pitied them.

08:35.162 --> 08:36.424
They felt sorry for them.

08:36.444 --> 08:38.868
So you could say, you'd be like, man, poor Benny, right?

08:39.288 --> 08:40.911
Poor Benny, everybody say poor Benny.

08:41.632 --> 08:42.713
Like, he can't walk.

08:43.154 --> 08:45.057
In Spanish, you would say, poor Benito.

08:45.858 --> 08:50.084
Benito, it rhymes.

08:50.104 --> 08:51.506
But what we're gonna see is that

08:52.322 --> 08:56.169
He might have been poor in health, but he was rich in relationships.

08:56.549 --> 09:00.195
He had four friends that didn't pity him, but they loved him.

09:00.256 --> 09:02.099
They cared for him.

09:02.119 --> 09:04.503
And I want to show you two truths, and here's the first one.

09:04.884 --> 09:08.690
A loving church carries burdens.

09:09.474 --> 09:11.577
A loving church carries burdens.

09:11.597 --> 09:13.540
So picture the scene, okay?

09:13.580 --> 09:14.902
The house is packed.

09:14.922 --> 09:17.726
I mean, from the windows to the walls, there's no room, right?

09:17.786 --> 09:20.450
And everybody's trying to get something from Jesus.

09:20.510 --> 09:21.732
Everybody wants something for him.

09:21.992 --> 09:28.622
But verse three says this, some man came bringing to Jesus a paralyzed man carried by four of them.

09:28.702 --> 09:32.488
Notice what his friends didn't say and what they didn't do.

09:32.568 --> 09:36.754
They didn't say, oh, Benny, I'll be praying for you.

09:37.794 --> 09:40.918
They didn't say, oh, Benny, I hope you find some help.

09:41.359 --> 09:42.240
No, what did they do?

09:42.781 --> 09:48.209
They picked him up, carried him, and brought him to Jesus.

09:49.090 --> 09:49.370
Why?

09:50.331 --> 09:52.915
Because love doesn't watch from the sidelines.

09:53.516 --> 09:55.759
Love carries the burden.

09:57.061 --> 10:01.347
Paul told the believers in Galatia to carry each other's burdens.

10:01.848 --> 10:05.593
And in this way, you will fulfill the law of Christ.

10:05.853 --> 10:06.514
In other words,

10:07.010 --> 10:11.875
Love doesn't just point people to Jesus, it carries them to Him.

10:12.755 --> 10:14.717
And this is important because you know this.

10:15.218 --> 10:19.061
People don't care how much you know until they know how much you care.

10:19.622 --> 10:31.293
And this matters now more than ever because if you're honest, if we just look at your feed, if you look at the news, we're seeing a world that's consumed with knowing more while caring less.

10:33.094 --> 10:36.978
And as Christ followers, we are in this world, but we're not of this world.

10:37.858 --> 10:43.265
And just let's just tell the truth, like we have access to unlimited information on our devices.

10:43.925 --> 10:48.591
And you gotta be careful to not just continue to fill your brain and lose your heart.

10:50.013 --> 10:52.095
The church is called to care.

10:53.437 --> 10:58.123
The church is called to love and as Christ followers, we're called to love others.

10:58.163 --> 11:00.646
We're called to carry the burdens.

11:01.747 --> 11:07.474
The world, the world is all about, let me prove you wrong and show you how I'm right.

11:08.674 --> 11:15.945
Like, you see that love proves that you care when you pick up the burden.

11:15.966 --> 11:19.371
And I'm so thankful for a church full of burden bearers.

11:20.012 --> 11:22.896
We got a church full of people that love to carry others.

11:22.916 --> 11:27.183
And I want to share with you three quick examples of some people that do this in our church.

11:27.263 --> 11:28.766
So, you know, the Uversion Bible Lab.

11:28.786 --> 11:30.268
How many of you got the Bible Lab?

11:30.288 --> 11:31.670
You got the Bible Lab, you love it, yeah?

11:32.051 --> 11:34.034
Did you know you could submit a prayer request in there?

11:34.306 --> 11:35.788
Yeah, you can submit prayer requests.

11:35.988 --> 11:37.791
So let me introduce you to Loveth.

11:37.951 --> 11:42.037
Loveth lives in Nigeria and she volunteers for you version.

11:42.057 --> 11:49.609
Loveth in six months has replied to and prayed with over 2,000 prayer requests, just in six months.

11:49.629 --> 11:52.853
She is a burden bearer, okay?

11:52.873 --> 11:56.018
The next one, next one is Casey.

11:56.194 --> 12:01.079
Casey, for two years, she's been writing, she volunteers with our Life Church online team.

12:01.099 --> 12:04.142
She's been writing to inmates who send us their stories.

12:04.402 --> 12:06.945
These are people that are incarcerated needing hope.

12:07.145 --> 12:09.087
And she's been writing to letters to them.

12:09.427 --> 12:14.132
Every single week, she reaches out and encourages them and shows them the love of Jesus.

12:14.733 --> 12:17.095
She is a burden bearer.

12:17.896 --> 12:19.057
And there's a third example.

12:19.838 --> 12:23.922
There's a family who found out they had no place to live.

12:24.034 --> 12:26.137
Another family in the church found this out.

12:26.658 --> 12:31.305
And so they said, hey, we've got like this little old trailer that we could just give this family.

12:31.325 --> 12:32.066
They could live there.

12:32.527 --> 12:35.811
So he gave it to them and they actually let them live on their property.

12:35.831 --> 12:39.236
I don't think that might be against the rules, but they let them live on their property.

12:39.296 --> 12:41.360
They carried the burdens.

12:42.121 --> 12:46.066
And it's just three examples of our church, people that carry burdens.

12:46.086 --> 12:48.610
See, when you love, you carry the burdens.

12:48.971 --> 12:53.938
And what's amazing to me is you can show that you care in so many different ways.

12:54.498 --> 12:59.886
Like, if someone's hurting, you can slow down and listen to them and pray for them.

13:00.928 --> 13:06.596
If someone's having a baby and nobody's throwing them a shower, you could be the one that says, hey, I'll throw you a baby shower.

13:06.616 --> 13:09.481
If somebody is sick, you can bring them a meal.

13:09.601 --> 13:10.863
Like, there's so many ways to see.

13:11.083 --> 13:17.192
Sometimes love looks big, and sometimes it looks small, but it's always personal.

13:17.973 --> 13:19.235
It's always personal.

13:19.696 --> 13:23.762
And what's amazing is that every single one of us has the potential to love

13:23.938 --> 13:24.659
like Jesus.

13:26.222 --> 13:27.083
You don't need a title.

13:27.704 --> 13:28.826
You don't need a platform.

13:29.046 --> 13:31.530
You don't even need to fix the problem.

13:31.570 --> 13:34.295
You just need to be willing to pick up the weight.

13:35.437 --> 13:39.684
Because when the church carries burdens, people experience the love of God.

13:40.385 --> 13:43.690
And when people experience the love of God, lives are changed.

13:44.431 --> 13:48.498
And a church that pleases God is made up of people who love

13:48.674 --> 13:49.395
like Jesus.

13:49.455 --> 13:51.017
So how does Jesus love?

13:51.038 --> 13:53.561
Jesus loves by carrying the burdens.

13:53.722 --> 13:55.003
And here's your second truth, okay?

13:55.023 --> 13:55.564
Write this down.

13:55.925 --> 14:00.151
Love breaks the rules to serve and save people.

14:01.493 --> 14:04.938
Love breaks the rules to serve and save people.

14:05.319 --> 14:06.641
Y'all rule followers right now.

14:06.661 --> 14:07.782
You're like, what?

14:09.745 --> 14:10.106
It does.

14:10.587 --> 14:12.850
Watch what Mark says in verse four.

14:13.826 --> 14:24.486
Since the four friends could not get him to Jesus because of the crowd, they made an opening in the roof above Jesus by digging through it and then lowered the mat that the man was laying out.

14:24.566 --> 14:28.594
Now, I know for a lot of us, we're thinking like, that's who created.

14:28.738 --> 14:29.799
It wasn't creative.

14:29.839 --> 14:31.000
It was crazy.

14:31.220 --> 14:34.123
Like they dug a hole in somebody's roof.

14:34.203 --> 14:36.906
And to us, it could sound creative, but it was not.

14:36.966 --> 14:41.950
And listen, I'm pretty sure property destruction was against the rules back then as it is now.

14:42.091 --> 14:46.635
And they didn't just break that rule, but they actually broke some social rules as well.

14:46.735 --> 14:49.317
Jesus was in the house and he was teaching.

14:49.377 --> 14:52.841
And you don't just break up or interrupt a conversation.

14:52.861 --> 14:56.284
And you definitely don't interrupt a rabbi who's teaching.

14:56.344 --> 14:57.865
They broke these rules.

14:57.965 --> 14:58.546
Why?

14:58.722 --> 15:03.328
because they loved their friend and what's crazier to me is that Jesus didn't stop them.

15:04.970 --> 15:07.333
He didn't say, hey, hey, hey, what are y'all doing?

15:07.553 --> 15:08.555
He didn't rebuke them.

15:10.077 --> 15:13.861
Jesus didn't look at them and say, hey, who's paying for that?

15:14.883 --> 15:15.183
Why?

15:15.223 --> 15:16.405
Why didn't he stop them?

15:17.166 --> 15:20.530
Because Jesus broke the rules for love too.

15:22.172 --> 15:26.898
Jesus, he ate with sinners and the Pharisees hated that.

15:27.778 --> 15:29.099
He forgave prostitutes.

15:29.160 --> 15:30.381
That was scandalous.

15:31.182 --> 15:32.343
He touched the lepers.

15:33.404 --> 15:34.866
He loved tax collectors.

15:34.946 --> 15:38.329
Jesus broke the rules for love.

15:38.350 --> 15:42.554
And in Mark's story, he tells us that Jesus saw something.

15:42.574 --> 15:43.395
Do you remember what he saw?

15:43.415 --> 15:44.376
Do you remember?

15:44.516 --> 15:45.698
You got to look closely, okay?

15:45.718 --> 15:46.979
I want you to see this right now.

15:46.999 --> 15:50.383
I want you to look at it because Jesus didn't focus on their wealth.

15:50.623 --> 15:52.205
He didn't focus on their acumen.

15:52.245 --> 15:54.727
He didn't focus on, do they have engineering degrees?

15:54.767 --> 15:56.069
He didn't focus on any of that.

15:56.089 --> 15:57.170
What did Jesus see?

15:57.506 --> 16:00.690
Jesus saw their faith.

16:02.633 --> 16:03.634
Jesus saw their faith.

16:05.297 --> 16:06.539
He saw their faith.

16:06.619 --> 16:10.724
Now, sometimes you hear read things in the description and you're like, what?

16:12.126 --> 16:13.308
Like, how do you see faith?

16:14.710 --> 16:15.992
How can you see faith?

16:16.873 --> 16:20.658
He saw their faith in actions expressed through love.

16:21.359 --> 16:22.360
See, it rules.

16:22.801 --> 16:24.163
Keep people from Jesus.

16:24.644 --> 16:26.386
Love finds another way.

16:28.226 --> 16:31.070
Now, let's pause here briefly, and let's just recap, okay?

16:31.691 --> 16:32.192
Here's what we got.

16:32.212 --> 16:33.293
We got a paralyzed man.

16:33.313 --> 16:37.920
We got Benny, and he needs healing, and he has four friends, and what do they do?

16:38.380 --> 16:42.166
They pick him up, carry him, and lowered him, right?

16:42.246 --> 16:43.147
So everybody say what they say.

16:43.207 --> 16:47.093
They picked him up, carried him, lowered him.

16:47.113 --> 16:48.074
Some of y'all ain't talking.

16:48.755 --> 16:49.897
I'm right here in person.

16:49.937 --> 16:50.517
I can see you.

16:50.537 --> 16:51.679
I'm not on the stream.

16:51.699 --> 16:54.042
So you guys in the chat, you can put that in there as well.

16:54.062 --> 16:56.626
So everybody together today, pick him up,

16:56.738 --> 16:59.521
Carried him and lowered him, okay?

17:00.102 --> 17:04.348
Now, this is important because I look at scripture and I'm like, wait a minute, hang on.

17:04.628 --> 17:10.075
Hold up one second, because I don't know how tall ceilings were back then, but let's just say seven feet.

17:11.016 --> 17:12.057
Sounds pretty good, right?

17:12.077 --> 17:14.140
Seven feet.

17:14.160 --> 17:17.764
So these four guys bring their friend and they dig a hole through their roof.

17:18.565 --> 17:19.266
And what do they do?

17:20.147 --> 17:23.271
They make this hole and they start lowering him down, right?

17:23.852 --> 17:25.554
Now at some point,

17:25.858 --> 17:29.601
You gotta believe there was a gap between Benny and the floor.

17:31.323 --> 17:37.249
The bottle doesn't say anything about a rope or any device, like they're just hanging on to Benny, right?

17:37.489 --> 17:42.574
And I just pictured the conversation going something like, hey, Benito, you trust us?

17:44.455 --> 17:45.176
Oh, yeah.

17:45.777 --> 17:49.140
And I say, hey, bro, I mean, Benny, I mean, he's already paralyzed.

17:49.160 --> 17:50.481
He's gonna get healed.

17:50.501 --> 17:55.826
So all three, one, two, they drop him, right?

17:56.002 --> 17:58.365
Like, let's just be honest, right?

17:59.686 --> 18:04.833
So they picked him up, say it with me, they picked him up, carried him, dropped him.

18:05.213 --> 18:07.756
Let's just call him what it is.

18:07.776 --> 18:07.876
Okay.

18:09.578 --> 18:10.840
So what does Jesus see?

18:10.880 --> 18:13.964
And what does he do?

18:13.984 --> 18:19.290
Jesus sees their faith and then he forgives his sins.

18:20.492 --> 18:22.354
He doesn't even heal them right then and there.

18:22.850 --> 18:24.672
He says, son, your sins are forgiven.

18:24.692 --> 18:27.735
Even with that statement, Jesus broke the rules.

18:27.775 --> 18:31.758
The Pharisees were saying, hey, hey, hey, only God can forgive sins.

18:33.600 --> 18:34.741
So here's my question for you.

18:36.083 --> 18:40.266
What rules do you need to break to bring someone to Jesus?

18:43.530 --> 18:52.498
Let's be honest, it's actually easier to carry the burdens and break the rules for someone you love than for someone you don't.

18:55.106 --> 19:00.835
Like, let me remind you that we're here in church and we're not supposed to lie.

19:02.538 --> 19:03.419
It's easier, right?

19:04.100 --> 19:09.028
It's easier to carry the burdens and to break the rules for someone you love and someone you don't.

19:10.390 --> 19:14.096
And as I was studying this story, it reminded me of a second guy.

19:14.617 --> 19:17.121
So this is your second story and your second guy.

19:17.642 --> 19:20.466
This guy also got picked up

19:20.610 --> 19:21.611
carried and dropped.

19:21.631 --> 19:23.754
And he does have a name, his name is Jonah.

19:23.814 --> 19:25.576
If you've been in church, you've heard Jonah's story.

19:25.916 --> 19:30.181
Even if you haven't been in church, you probably heard some story about a guy getting swallowed up by a fish.

19:30.441 --> 19:34.526
You might have heard of it, but let me take just about 60 seconds and tell you the story really quickly.

19:34.546 --> 19:36.207
So you won't have to listen fast, okay?

19:36.227 --> 19:37.209
So listen fast, all right?

19:37.229 --> 19:40.112
So Jonah is a man of God, okay?

19:40.132 --> 19:47.941
And God tells him, Jonah, I need you to go to the Ninevites who are evil people, and I need you to tell them to repent, or I'm gonna destroy them.

19:47.961 --> 19:49.202
Now, when I say evil,

19:49.346 --> 19:50.627
That doesn't you do it justice.

19:50.647 --> 19:52.950
Like these were horrible evil people.

19:53.050 --> 19:57.334
I'm talking about child sacrifices, torturing people, heads on stake.

19:57.354 --> 20:00.777
They were evil and the entire world hated the Ninevites.

20:00.817 --> 20:04.341
And Jonah also didn't like them.

20:04.361 --> 20:04.962
He didn't like them.

20:06.723 --> 20:08.345
And so God tells him, go tell him this.

20:08.565 --> 20:09.286
Go tell him.

20:09.306 --> 20:10.407
Jonah knows who God is.

20:10.467 --> 20:12.229
God is gracious.

20:12.629 --> 20:13.150
God is good.

20:13.930 --> 20:15.832
And he thinks, well, what if they repent?

20:15.872 --> 20:16.633
He's gonna forgive them.

20:16.733 --> 20:17.554
I don't want that.

20:17.634 --> 20:18.475
So what does Jonah do?

20:18.675 --> 20:19.776
He disobeys God.

20:19.796 --> 20:23.920
He goes in the opposite direction, gets on a ship and starts sailing in the opposite direction.

20:24.180 --> 20:27.203
But how many of you know sometimes God will break the rules to get your attention?

20:28.244 --> 20:30.867
I don't know what the weather forecast was, but they didn't expect the storm.

20:30.907 --> 20:33.710
God sends a storm and the ship is getting tossed around.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.211
All the ship meets are going crazy.

20:35.231 --> 20:35.872
What is going to happen?

20:35.912 --> 20:36.593
What's happening?

20:36.613 --> 20:37.473
They wake up Jonah.

20:37.494 --> 20:39.996
Jonah wakes up and he's like, sorry guys, my bad.

20:40.036 --> 20:40.737
This is on me.

20:42.338 --> 20:43.039
And so what do they do?

20:43.339 --> 20:46.162
They pick them up, carried him.

20:46.530 --> 20:48.152
Drop them in the ocean, right?

20:48.713 --> 20:49.774
The storm calms down.

20:49.794 --> 20:51.817
A big fish comes, swallows him up.

20:51.857 --> 20:55.622
Three days, three nights in the belly of the fish, drops them on the shore.

20:56.003 --> 21:00.208
Jonah stands in front of the Ninevites and he's like, fine, I'll tell him.

21:01.009 --> 21:03.773
So he gets up there and he says, repent, turn or burn.

21:06.457 --> 21:09.421
And I could imagine him just kind of stepping away and saying, all right, I did it.

21:09.941 --> 21:10.662
Smite them.

21:11.904 --> 21:12.965
Strike them down.

21:15.649 --> 21:16.530
You know it's crazy.

21:17.762 --> 21:18.723
It's crazy what happens.

21:19.804 --> 21:20.545
They repent.

21:22.607 --> 21:24.249
Watch what Jonah 3, 10 says.

21:26.411 --> 21:27.813
When God did what?

21:29.394 --> 21:33.159
When God saw... Sound familiar?

21:34.079 --> 21:39.345
Jesus saw when God saw what they did and how they turned from their evil ways.

21:39.485 --> 21:43.249
He relented and did not bring on them the destruction he had threatened.

21:44.951 --> 21:47.634
He saw.

21:49.346 --> 21:50.087
And he forgave.

21:50.127 --> 21:55.757
So one guy needs Jesus.

21:56.939 --> 21:59.023
One guy is called to preach.

21:59.844 --> 22:04.632
Both get picked up, carried, and dropped.

22:04.652 --> 22:06.035
So let's just call it what it is.

22:07.397 --> 22:10.763
Most of us, we don't need to dig holes in roofs.

22:11.504 --> 22:15.090
We need to make heart, room in our heart for people that we don't like.

22:17.826 --> 22:18.807
There are people you don't like.

22:18.847 --> 22:19.648
Let's just be honest.

22:21.009 --> 22:21.550
Gossippers.

22:22.751 --> 22:23.712
Anybody like a gossiper?

22:24.232 --> 22:24.412
No.

22:25.253 --> 22:26.194
Self-centered people?

22:26.414 --> 22:26.594
No.

22:27.275 --> 22:27.776
One uppers?

22:28.697 --> 22:29.277
One downers?

22:30.018 --> 22:30.799
Android users?

22:35.103 --> 22:36.364
Green bubbles, ah!

22:39.587 --> 22:41.969
All joking aside, we have to be honest.

22:42.009 --> 22:46.834
There are certain types of people, certain groups, certain individuals,

22:47.362 --> 22:51.487
that you don't like and that you maybe even hate.

22:54.170 --> 22:57.494
See, the world is growing more and more hateful.

22:58.455 --> 23:02.941
The rules are clear on who you're supposed to like and who you're supposed to hate.

23:04.282 --> 23:07.626
If you're this political party, you hate this political party.

23:08.487 --> 23:10.950
If you're this race, you hate this race.

23:12.192 --> 23:14.955
If someone in your family hurts you, it's okay to hate them.

23:16.217 --> 23:17.298
And let me just be clear.

23:17.538 --> 23:19.280
This isn't just an America thing.

23:19.521 --> 23:20.843
This happens all over the world.

23:21.083 --> 23:31.117
There are countries that for centuries, if not thousands of years, you've been told those people we don't like.

23:31.137 --> 23:36.705
If you're honest, you might even think to yourself, who is deserving of God's love?

23:36.945 --> 23:40.109
And you might think, well, not those people.

23:40.129 --> 23:46.258
See, the world is growing more hateful, but you got to break the rules.

23:46.946 --> 23:53.176
Your rules, society norms, you gotta break the rules to love people to Jesus.

23:53.256 --> 23:56.482
The world says hate them, fear them.

23:57.363 --> 23:59.506
But this book says love your neighbor.

24:00.248 --> 24:02.511
This book says lay down your life.

24:03.072 --> 24:05.556
This book says give God's love away.

24:05.917 --> 24:07.680
Be generous with your love.

24:07.700 --> 24:13.970
And as Christ followers, we're called to live by His Word, not by what the world says.

24:16.130 --> 24:19.915
Are you willing to love people that you might not even like?

24:21.436 --> 24:23.939
Some of us are waiting for the world to become more loving.

24:24.240 --> 24:27.644
Some of us might be waiting for the system to become more caring.

24:27.864 --> 24:29.406
It's time to stop waiting.

24:29.446 --> 24:31.689
It's time to start loving.

24:35.553 --> 24:41.601
And as your pastor, I think about our church.

24:43.663 --> 24:45.906
I think about the beauty of our church.

24:46.754 --> 24:48.156
the faces of our church.

24:49.157 --> 25:00.349
And I think about how many of you are people who care and carry each other's burdens, people who are willing to do anything short of sin to reach people for Jesus.

25:00.389 --> 25:08.078
I think about a church of people who don't just care, they carry the burdens, who don't just follow the rules, but they rescue people.

25:10.000 --> 25:15.346
Maybe today you need someone to carry you and remind you

25:15.746 --> 25:16.527
of your purpose.

25:18.329 --> 25:21.593
That your purpose is to love even those you may not like.

25:21.653 --> 25:22.034
Why?

25:22.134 --> 25:22.414
Why?

25:22.855 --> 25:23.636
Why does this matter?

25:23.696 --> 25:26.499
Why is this important?

25:26.519 --> 25:27.641
Because it's all for the one.

25:29.403 --> 25:30.304
It's all for the one.

25:32.366 --> 25:34.909
It's because there's still room for one more.

25:34.949 --> 25:37.412
One more hurting person.

25:38.173 --> 25:41.818
One more person that's far from God that needs healing and hope.

25:41.858 --> 25:43.660
There's room for one more.

25:43.700 --> 25:45.202
It's all about the one.

25:46.850 --> 25:47.251
Why?

25:47.291 --> 25:50.735
Because at one point, you were the one.

25:52.317 --> 25:53.239
I was the one.

25:54.761 --> 25:56.764
You were the one that needed to be carried.

25:56.804 --> 25:59.107
I was the one that needed to be loved.

26:00.509 --> 26:01.370
It's all about the one.

26:02.932 --> 26:07.158
I think back to just in my life, how many times the church has loved me.

26:07.658 --> 26:16.210
I think of about our first baby that we had a miscarriage and lost our baby and that spiraled me into depression and anxiety and loneliness and

26:16.994 --> 26:18.838
secret sin and shame.

26:19.859 --> 26:23.546
It wasn't until I went to a pastor and just told him everything that was happening.

26:23.567 --> 26:25.210
And that pastor picked me up.

26:25.250 --> 26:27.474
He carried me and he laid me down.

26:27.534 --> 26:32.644
He dropped me at the feet of Jesus to find healing, to become whole, to be made new.

26:33.085 --> 26:35.890
And I think about 15 years ago,

26:36.162 --> 26:45.157
When I picked up my family from Los Angeles and moved to Oklahoma City and Life Church loved us and cared for us and accepted us and embraced us.

26:45.177 --> 26:53.510
And I think about my pastors, Pastor Craig and Amy, who we just celebrated 30 years, 30 years ago, they planted a church that broke the rules.

26:53.570 --> 27:00.882
People told them you can't do that in church, but they broke the rules to create a place where everyone can come just as they are.

27:01.442 --> 27:06.989
I think about my leaders who are breaking some rules by even letting me stand on this stage.

27:07.009 --> 27:07.409
Why?

27:07.429 --> 27:10.012
Because I don't have a seminary degree.

27:10.273 --> 27:14.478
I dropped out of college right before I graduated, found paper, by the rules.

27:14.698 --> 27:20.185
I'm not qualified to stand up here, but they broke the rules because of God's anointing and his grace.

27:20.425 --> 27:24.290
And by his favor, I'm able to stand on this stage and give you God's word.

27:26.352 --> 27:27.634
It's all about the one.

27:30.786 --> 27:34.830
And I think about it just even in my childhood, because remember that trailer?

27:34.890 --> 27:36.272
Remember that family?

27:37.013 --> 27:38.014
That was my family.

27:39.235 --> 27:40.456
Somebody did that for us.

27:41.498 --> 27:42.959
Somebody gave us a place to live.

27:43.980 --> 27:45.182
Somebody cared for us.

27:45.682 --> 27:54.191
And if he did that for me, I want to lay my life down, reaching one more, doing anything to care for the one.

27:54.752 --> 27:55.813
And you can too.

27:56.974 --> 27:57.815
You can do it too.

27:58.396 --> 28:00.338
You can love people, all people.

28:00.706 --> 28:07.753
You can pick them up, you can carry them, and you can lay them at the feet of Jesus, loving them to Christ.

28:07.773 --> 28:22.406
And in this way, if we do this, look, online, if we do this together, if you love people to Jesus, if I love people to Jesus, we go from being people who please God to being a church that pleases God.

28:22.446 --> 28:24.809
And that is what we are gonna be.

28:25.369 --> 28:29.593
We're gonna be a church that pleases God.

28:29.613 --> 28:30.674
So God, we thank you.

28:32.002 --> 28:40.010
Thank you that you are a good, loving Father, that you loved us, Father God, when nobody else would.

28:41.912 --> 29:00.690
As we pray today, I recognize that there are some of you here today that even just thinking about your pain and the pain that you've experienced in your life, I can understand that it can be hard to have love in your heart for that person who betrayed you,

29:01.826 --> 29:11.959
that person who abused you, that person who hurt you, the people that labeled you, I can understand it can be hard to have love for them.

29:13.381 --> 29:25.015
But if you'll come to your Heavenly Father and ask Him, He will miraculously give you the ability to love them.

29:25.036 --> 29:30.162
Today, as we pray, if you're here and you say, you know what?

29:31.778 --> 29:33.681
I want Jesus to make me more loving.

29:35.664 --> 29:37.667
I want him to make me more loving person.

29:38.308 --> 29:41.874
If that's you, and I hope this is everyone here today, would you just raise your hand?

29:42.195 --> 29:45.480
I wanna pray for you, say, yeah, I want Jesus to make me more loving.

29:45.500 --> 29:48.124
God, would you make us a loving church, Father God?

29:48.525 --> 29:50.207
Would you make us a loving people, Lord?

29:51.169 --> 29:53.012
God, that we would love others towards you.

29:53.853 --> 29:59.442
Lord, even the people that we may not connect with, the people that we are far from, the people that just,

29:59.650 --> 30:04.656
look different, Father God, Lord, that you would just put your love in our hearts for them.

30:05.817 --> 30:16.809
That we would remember that they're the one that you cared for, that the good shepherd leaves the 99 to go after the one, to pick up the one, to carry the one and bring them home.

30:16.869 --> 30:21.394
And so would you use us to love the one that's far from you?

30:22.796 --> 30:25.239
As we continue praying, nobody looking around.

30:25.279 --> 30:28.242
There are those of you here today that

30:28.674 --> 30:35.743
As you hear about this love from God, if you're honest, you might say, listen, I don't know that God could love someone like me.

30:36.805 --> 30:38.006
I've made a lot of mistakes.

30:38.167 --> 30:39.609
I've done a lot of bad things.

30:39.689 --> 30:40.510
I've hurt people.

30:41.050 --> 30:42.412
There's just no way God could love me.

30:43.714 --> 30:45.837
Let me just tell you, I understand where you're at.

30:47.139 --> 30:47.739
I was there too.

30:48.580 --> 30:52.786
I felt like my sins disqualified me from a loving God.

30:54.018 --> 30:57.483
And if I can just be honest with you, we were to just sit down and have a conversation.

30:57.523 --> 30:59.567
And I ask you, hey, do you know God's love?

31:00.368 --> 31:01.570
Have you surrendered to Him?

31:02.251 --> 31:03.333
Have you found healing?

31:04.154 --> 31:08.461
If you were honest, you might say things like, wow, I don't know where I stand with God.

31:08.481 --> 31:09.522
Let me just tell you right now.

31:10.023 --> 31:11.205
God loves you so much.

31:11.806 --> 31:14.390
And He knew that our sin would separate us from Him.

31:14.450 --> 31:15.472
And so He did something.

31:15.752 --> 31:16.754
He broke the rules.

31:16.814 --> 31:20.660
He sent His son Jesus, who lived a perfect life.

31:21.060 --> 31:22.162
He did not sin.

31:22.786 --> 31:25.309
And Jesus did something for us that we could not do.

31:26.451 --> 31:28.073
Jesus broke the rules for you.

31:29.294 --> 31:35.682
Jesus picked up the cross, carried it, and laid his life down for love.

31:36.643 --> 31:38.185
He did it because he loved you.

31:39.307 --> 31:48.178
And scripture tells us that anyone who calls on Christ, anyone who turns from their sin, repents from their sin, and turns towards God.

31:48.642 --> 31:50.124
would be saved, would be forgiven.

31:50.144 --> 31:52.647
And for many of you, that's actually why you're here today.

31:52.707 --> 31:57.633
It's to turn away from your sins, to repent, to say, God, I need you in my life.

31:58.014 --> 32:00.217
I need your forgiveness and your grace.

32:00.237 --> 32:01.779
And that is why you're here.

32:01.859 --> 32:03.641
And so in a moment, I'm gonna count to three.

32:03.661 --> 32:08.928
And when I get to three of that's you, I want you to raise your hand up, to say, yes, I need Jesus.

32:09.068 --> 32:11.231
I'm a sinner in need of a savior.

32:11.251 --> 32:13.213
And if that's you, I'm gonna count to three when I get to three.

32:13.574 --> 32:15.416
I want you to lift your hand up right now.

32:15.637 --> 32:16.818
One, God loves you.

32:16.898 --> 32:17.919
He's here for you today.

32:18.300 --> 32:20.203
Ready to forgive you and give you a new life too.

32:20.543 --> 32:21.485
Don't wait for tomorrow.

32:21.525 --> 32:23.167
Tomorrow's not promised to anyone.

32:23.548 --> 32:25.691
Today is your day of salvation.

32:26.051 --> 32:28.114
Three, come on, lift your hand up right now and look up.

32:28.154 --> 32:29.055
I see you there.

32:29.356 --> 32:31.058
God bless you here in the front.

32:31.078 --> 32:31.639
God is with you.

32:31.659 --> 32:32.601
I got you right there, brother.

32:32.641 --> 32:33.982
New life in Christ.

32:34.563 --> 32:35.465
Others that say yes.

32:35.645 --> 32:38.068
Those of you online, just type it in the chat.

32:38.769 --> 32:42.615
I give my life to Jesus as we surrender to Jesus today.

32:42.635 --> 32:43.556
I got you right here as well.

32:43.576 --> 32:44.818
God bless you, brother.

32:45.026 --> 32:48.751
Come on church, you should be celebrating big as people turn to Jesus.

32:50.993 --> 32:55.118
We're gonna pray together, those of you online, just repeat this prayer with us.

32:55.178 --> 33:00.104
Say, Heavenly Father, Almighty God, I give you my life.

33:01.026 --> 33:02.187
I surrender my heart.

33:03.328 --> 33:08.234
Today I declare Jesus as my Lord and my Savior.

33:09.075 --> 33:10.217
I receive your love.

33:11.338 --> 33:14.482
Fill me with your spirit so I can follow you.

33:14.818 --> 33:18.642
serve you and love others like you love me.

33:19.664 --> 33:20.745
Thank you for that love.

33:21.546 --> 33:22.587
Thank you for new life.

33:23.428 --> 33:24.549
Now you have mine.

33:25.390 --> 33:26.732
In Jesus name, I pray.

33:26.812 --> 33:28.694
Somebody get a little crazy.

33:29.094 --> 33:30.396
Somebody get a little loud.

33:31.057 --> 33:33.179
Come on, celebrate new life in Jesus today.

33:33.219 --> 33:36.002
Come on.

33:36.022 --> 33:39.406
We are celebrating with those of you who just made the decision to follow Jesus.

33:39.807 --> 33:42.610
Check out the show notes for helpful resources and next steps.

33:43.010 --> 33:49.138
Remember to head over to life.church slash podcast connect to share a little about yourself and how we can support you.

